        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "I have an old code part which uses Zend_Validate::is() to validate form entries (it is pre Zend_Form code). First of all, have a look at it:\n\nif (! Zend_Validate::is($postValue, $v, $validatorArgs, array('My_Validate'))) {\n\t...\n}\n\nfunc_get_args() array(4) {\n  [0] => string(2) \"02\"\n  [1] => string(3) \"Int\"\n  [2] => array(2) {\n    [\"min\"] => int(1)\n    [\"max\"] => int(31)\n  }\n  [3] => array(1) {\n    [0] => string(11) \"My_Validate\"\n  }\n}\n\nWhen it comes to validate with \"Int\", I'll get (with some debugging) the following exception:\n\nThe locale '1' is no known locale\n\nThis message comes from Zend_Locale::findLocale().\n\nIf I see it right, then Zend_Validate::is() calls the __construct() method if available with $args - which would result in the paramater\narray(2) {\n    [\"min\"] => int(1)\n    [\"max\"] => int(31)\n  }\nfrom fun_get_args(). But Zend_Validate_Int needs a locale as parameter for the constructor."
        },
